text.full: Good food, service and great choices of your favorite beverage! Bobbie's Bolognese is the best!

What's not to love about this place?

I have been here several times with several people and they never disappoint. 

The pastas here are some of the best I've had in the Seattle area. They make everything out of sourdough and that flavor really pops through especially in the pasta. 

The damn good wings are true to their name. We order them every time we're here! 

Their cocktails are really nice too, I had the espresso martini on a Sunday afternoon and I would totally love to repeat that. 

Also this place is massive! I've almost always been seated without a reservation. But be wary, there's a show venue close by so the place tends to get packed on show nights. 

Bring Seattle visitors here after hitting up Pike Place, they will totally love it.

Found this gem thanks to yelp. Was very busy as there was baseball, hockey, and NCAA basketball playing. Sat at the bar. Drinks were great and bartenders very polite and interactive. We trued the burger and a chicken parm sandwich and both were excellent. Portions are huge- definitely could have shared. Will be back next time were in Seattle.

Chicken parm sandwich. A bit spicy but soooo good.

text.full: George was great! Very attentive and kind. Checked for my allergies and overall a great experience. Will be coming back just for him! If it's not George, I don't want it!

So happy I stumbled this place on a TikTok post! delicious food and cool  ambience. It's a great way to end a long weekend trip to Seattle, as a souvenir bought a package of their sourdough pasta to cook at home !
My favorite place to eat always. HH is great and to top it off service is amazing, particularly our boy Connor who was prompt, kind and fun.
Wonderful experience as always at Vons. Anastasia was a phenomenal server. Very attentive and made our visit enjoyable.

It was a good service and a good time. I ordered the chop salad, which was a small portion but very filling. The spirits menu is extensive and fun. Overall was a very enjoyable experience for a Friday night dinner. The burger was juicy and well cooked.

The food was delicious and service was great! Clean inside, great location. I am not from Seattle and thought this was a great restaurant to try when visiting. Would love to go back and try more dishes!

text.full:
I dined at Vons 1000 on two separate occasions--once for lunch and once for dinner, and both times were FANTASTIC!   

For lunch, I had the Spiced Fig, Prosciutto, and Arugula Sourdough Pizza. The combination of  mozzarella, goat cheese, and almond pesto was such a delightful twist. Every bite was a perfect mix of savory and sweet.

For dinner, I had the Tellicherry Chicken & Smoked Gouda Pasta. The chicken was tender. The sourdough was amazing... all swimming in a creamy sauce that had just the right kick from the pepper. It was comfort food at its best!

Located right by Pike Place Market, Vons 1000 is definitely a must-visit in Seattle. The atmosphere was inviting, and the staff was super friendly. I can't wait to go back.

text.full:
Super cramped especially if you're in the bar area and super expensive ..  I came twice once for dinner and lunch. For drinks they have a special that's suppose to be the best deal in town $8 for a martini and another cocktail I didn't recall. I was going to order but they make a point of saying no returns.  What if I don't like it. It's it suppose to be your pass to make a a crappy drink knowing we can't return it.  I ended up having a beer and then on my return an old Fashion. Both were good and I would have again.  For food I tried the Cuban sandwhich. The smoked gouda gnocchi and the  fig pizza.   The best was the pasta dish  I hands down recommended. if you can get a seat away from
The crazy bar area.  I do want to say during lunch the bar area was ok. At night though you can barely move and you have to go through the bar to get to the restaurant. Pizza was decent not bad but I have had better.

Great staff and good happy hour specials. Nice atmosphere 
Food was OK, not great. I had the chicken nuggets or strips or whatever they were hiding under that tasty enough but sweet sauce. Mediocre quality hidden by a heavy sauce.
I had the best server George who went above and beyond taking care of me. He is a gem and would come back to this restaurant just to be served by his joyful presence.

text.full: Chris was our waiter and he was FANTASTIC! Incredibly fast, funny and only elevated our dining experience. I had a delicious pasta dish with foccia bread reccomended from Chris and it was amazing! Our group of four had a great time. Incredible service, drinks and food

Ron was an amazing server he made our time so much better and fun. The food was amazing we order a whipped cherve and sundried tomato pizza and wings and they were to die for so delicious. The ambiance is fun and laid back very nice. Overall my husband and I had an amazing time! Stop by if you have you are in the area !! :)
Connor was an amazing server!! Quick service and very kind. The food was amazing! Love this restaurant! The vibes are the best!

text.full: I have come to Von's for a few years now when I have friends in town and want a fun environment and good drinks. I'm writing now because I appreciate the service of my bartender Jess. Her care and concern saved my friend from burning his luscious locks when he got the drink with a sparkler, as he was tempted to try and chug it immediately thanks to the deficiencies in the public education system in the US. Jess was fabulous and made our time more enjoyable! Definitely recommend checking this place out!

Amazing restaurant! I thought this is just one of those corporate dinner spots in downtown Seattle and did not expect much however, they really exceeded my expectation and deliver such a great dinner!!

The appetizers were great to start with. The chicken was very tender, but flavorful for on trees I was completely mind blown by might help make pasta with salmon. The salmon was extremely tender and not fishy. The flavor went well, and the texture complimented the pasta. This dish is something that the chefs should definitely be proud of!!!!!

Amazing spot and I will definitely come back
Go here. You won't regret it! The food and drinks were amazing. I was sitting under the drink wheel and the server asked me to spin it. A good time.

I tried to make reservations ahead of time but there wasn't any available. When I got there I was told it was a 30-45 minute wait. I put my name on the list. I kept checking my phone periodically to see if I would get a text and never did. After 50 minutes, I walked inside and asked about the wait and they said they sent a text. I did not receive any text and I asked to verify the number they entered because I'm pretty sure they entered it incorrectly. They need to repeat back to confirm to avoid any miscommunication. Either way, there was a table available when I asked. 
The server was nice and welcoming. We placed our order right away because we had time while we're waiting to go over the menu. Our food came out within 15 minutes, which was nice. The burger I ordered, Classic Seattle, was huge. It looked so juicy and loaded. I took a bite and it didn't disappoint. Can't go wrong with that if you're wanting a good burger. I tried the chicken pasta and it was delicious. The pasta was soft and perfect texture and the creamy sauce with the bites of chicken were amazing. The four meat pizza was a good size. It's pretty shareable for 2 to 3 people. I recommend getting it with zesty sauce. There was so much flavor with the melty cheese, meats and the dough was super soft. The three items we ordered were 5/5 .

Delicious food and I highly recommend when in the area.

Well, I don't know if Alex (manager, or coach of sorts, or whatever he is called) woke up on the wrong side of the bed or someone pee'd in his coffee, but he's rude and has a bad attitude toward customers. What are the odds that our first time there he treats us badly. We've been to less expensive places where we were treated 10 times better. Not going back and get treated that way.

Went to Vons for my 26th Birthday, the employees were great and the ambiance was nice. I had the steak & chips, and let me tell you the steak was awesome! My bartender Chris took very good care of me and made sure my birthday was special!
I 10/10 recommend this place for anyone living or visiting in Seattle!
Everything was great! We had the crispy bang bang chicken, carnitas and avocado pizzas and the 4 meat pizza. Service was great as well!

I wish the experience at Von's would have been better. The food was great of course but the service was poor. Our waiter Patrick was not welcoming/friendly nor did he acknowledge us until I said something. It appeared as if we were a bother to him by just asking questions about the menu. Completely took away from the experience of this highly rated pizza place. We were so excited to try this restaurant but unfortunately won't be back. I understand we never know what people are going through but his interactions with other customers was completely different than what we experienced.
Nate was a fantastic care coordinator at Von's. We enjoyed the conversation and the service! Thank you Nate!
Food was okay , ordered 2 burgers with side salads 4 drinks and paid around 160 , also was happy hour so kinda pricey for what we got . Would not recommend to friend .

We had a family dinner and everyone was very happy with their choices: cod tacos, salmon burger, chicken parm sandwich, salmon chowder. Portions were huge but we ate it all - it was super tasty! Had bohemian lager and it was good too. Our waiter was very kind and helpful. Ambiance is casual and comfortable.

If you are looking for good food AND great service come to Vons. George is the MAN. He made my last meal of the day a 10/10. Food is awesome too. Bang bang chicken was great, and we got the carnitas and avocado pizza.

businessPhotos.caption: George has probably the best customer service out of any server I have had during my stay here in Seattle.
